<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n10051f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10051f">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10051f"> 51(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> superscription / circum &mdash; dispatch</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Sur la proposition du nouveau directeur, une ordonnance royale, rendue &agrave; la date du 16 octobre 1627, enjoignit &ldquo;&agrave; tout destinataire de lettres et de paquets, de payer sans contestation ni r&eacute;plique les sommes que les agents d&apos;intendance leur r&eacute;clameraient pour les ports desdits envois&rdquo;. En vertu d&apos;une ordonnance en date du 18 mai 1630, diverses <mark>circonscriptions</mark> administratives de Paris et de quelques villes, re&ccedil;urent des <mark>bureaux de d&eacute;p&ecirc;ches</mark> que devaient diriger des &ldquo;maistres de courriers, relevant eux-m&ecirc;mes de contr&ocirc;leurs principaux&rdquo;. <font color="green">[On the new Postmaster General&apos;s proposal, a royal ordinance of 16 October 1627, directed &ldquo;all recipients of letters and packages to pay without dispute or retort the sums that the official agents requested of them for the delivery of the aforesaid mails&rdquo;. In pursuance of an ordinance dated May 18, 1630, various administrative districts of Paris and a few other large cities received offices of dispatches that were to be controlled by &ldquo;the masters of the couriers, themselves within the jurisdiction of the principal superintendents&rdquo;.]</font> <small> Eug&egrave;ne Gallois, <a name="EGLP" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EGLP"><cite title="source">La Poste</cite></a> (1894) 104-5</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
